ro for serious ecommerce Hybrid Approach: EasySite for prototyping, migrate to Shopify Alternative: Custom development if very specific needs 7. Implementation Resources Complete reference list Next steps Documentation links Key Insights from Analysis: ✅ What EasySite CAN do: Basic product catalog Simple checkout (with third-party integrations) AI chatbot for customer service Drag-and-drop editing ❌ What EasySite CANNOT do (compared to Falcon Pro): Quantity breaks pricing 3-tier cart goals Advanced upsell/cross-sell systems Subscription upgrades Bundle builders Low-stock indicators Variant switchers in cart Delivery date calculators Sub-1-second load times Straight Talk Recommendation: Don't try to force EasySite.ai into being something it's not. It's an AI website cloner/generator, not a dedicated ecommerce platform. For serious ecommerce with conversion optimization: Go with Shopify + Falcon Pro. The $479 one-time investment pays for itself quickly with the built-in CRO features that would cost $100-300/month in third-party apps on other platforms. Use EasySite for: Quick prototypes, testing concepts, non-ecommerce sites, or if you're just experimenting before committing to a full ecommerce solution. The document is formatted professionally with color-coded feature availability, detailed tables, and tactical implementation steps exactly as you specified in your profile preferences. Falcon Pro vs AI Website Builders Comprehensive Analysis Click to open Edit in AI Docs Executive Summary: Can AI Website Builders Match Falcon Pro's Ecommerce Power? Short Answer: No - Neither EasySite.ai nor EZSite.ai can currently replicate the full ecommerce functionality of the Falcon Pro Shopify theme. Strategic Assessment: While AI website builders excel at rapid deployment and basic functionality, they fall significantly short of enterprise-level ecommerce capabilities that Falcon Pro delivers. Key Findings & Strategic Recommendations Critical Feature Gaps Analysis Falcon Pro Cap